  <article class="card card--comfortable" aria-labelledby="privacy-policy-title">
    <h1 id="privacy-policy-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> April 27, 2026</p>

    <p>
      This Privacy Policy describes how <strong>Musifer, operated by Everett Ballance</strong>
      ("Musifer," "we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and shares information when you visit
      musifer.studio, contact us, or otherwise interact with this website (the "Site").
    </p>

    <h2>1. Scope</h2>
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy applies to information collected through this Site and any contact forms
      or other direct communications connected to this Site.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We aim to collect as little personal information as reasonably possible.</p>

    <h3>Information you provide directly</h3>
    <p>We may collect information that you choose to provide, such as:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>your name</li>
      <li>your email address</li>
      <li>the contents of any message you send us</li>
      <li>any other information you voluntarily include in a contact form or email</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
    <p>
      When you visit the Site, certain technical information may be collected automatically by our
      hosting provider or analytics tools, such as:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>IP address or truncated/anonymized IP information</li>
      <li>browser type and device information</li>
      <li>pages visited</li>
      <li>referring website</li>
      <li>approximate traffic and usage metrics</li>
      <li>date and time of access</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      We do <strong>not</strong> use the Site to sell personal data, build advertising profiles, or
      engage in cross-site behavioral tracking.
    </p>

    <h2>3. How We Use Information</h2>
    <p>We may use information we collect to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>operate, maintain, and improve the Site</li>
      <li>respond to messages, inquiries, or requests</li>
      <li>understand general Site traffic and performance</li>
      <li>detect, prevent, or address security or technical issues</li>
      <li>comply with applicable legal obligations</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Analytics</h2>
    <p>We may use privacy-focused analytics tools to understand overall Site traffic and performance.</p>

    <p><strong>Current analytics setup:</strong> We use Umami analytics for site-level traffic measurement.</p>
    <p><strong>Cookies used for analytics:</strong> No</p>
    <p>
      <strong>IP handling in analytics:</strong> We use analytics for aggregate reporting and do not use
      analytics data to identify individual visitors. We do not use full IP addresses in analytics
      reports, and IP data may still be processed transiently by hosting/analytics infrastructure for
      request handling and security.
    </p>
    <p><strong>Personal profiling:</strong> No</p>
    <p><strong>Advertising or remarketing use:</strong> No</p>

    <h2>5. Cookies and Similar Technologies</h2>
    <p>The Site may use essential technical measures needed for basic operation and security.</p>

    <p>
      We do not use cookies for advertising or cross-site tracking, and our current first-party
      analytics setup is intended to operate without analytics cookies.
    </p>

    <p>
      Third-party services embedded in or loaded by the Site (for example media platforms) may set
      their own cookies or similar technologies under their own policies.
    </p>

    <p>You can usually control cookies through your browser settings.</p>

    <h2>6. Sharing of Information</h2>
    <p>We do not sell personal information.</p>

    <p>We may share information only in limited circumstances, such as:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        with service providers that help us operate the Site, such as hosting, form handling, or
        analytics providers
      </li>
      <li>when necessary to protect the security or integrity of the Site</li>
      <li>when required by law, legal process, or a valid governmental request</li>
      <li>
        in connection with a business transfer, if the Site or related assets are transferred in the
        future
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>
      The Site may rely on third-party services for hosting, analytics, embedded content, form
      processing, email delivery, or similar functions.
    </p>

    <p>Examples may include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Hosting:</strong> Vercel</li>
      <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Umami</li>
      <li><strong>Forms / email delivery:</strong> Delivery via Microsoft Graph</li>
      <li><strong>Embedded content:</strong> SoundCloud, YouTube</li>
      <li><strong>Fonts and static assets:</strong> Google Fonts (fonts.googleapis.com, fonts.gstatic.com)</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      These third parties may process technical information as necessary to provide their services.
      Embedded platforms and external vendors may collect data independently when their content or
      resources are loaded. Their handling of data is governed by their own privacy policies and
      practices.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>
      We keep personal information only for as long as reasonably necessary for the purposes described
      in this Policy, including:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>responding to communications</li>
      <li>maintaining Site functionality</li>
      <li>preserving security records</li>
      <li>meeting legal, tax, or administrative obligations</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      If you contact us and later want your message or related personal information deleted, you may
      request that we do so, subject to any legal or operational need to retain it.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Your Choices</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on your location and applicable law, you may have the right to request access to,
      correction of, deletion of, or information about the personal data we hold about you.
    </p>

    <p>You may also:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>choose not to submit contact forms or other information</li>
      <li>contact us to request deletion of information you previously provided</li>
      <li>configure your browser to block or clear cookies, where applicable</li>
    </ul>

    <p>To make a privacy-related request, contact us using the information below.</p>

    <h2>10. Do Not Track</h2>
    <p>
      Some browsers offer a "Do Not Track" setting. Because there is no universally accepted standard
      for how to respond to these signals, the Site may not respond to Do Not Track requests unless
      otherwise stated.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      This Site is not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal
      information from children under 13 through the Site. If you believe a child has provided personal
      information through the Site, contact us so we can review and delete it as appropriate.
    </p>

    <h2>12. Security</h2>
    <p>
      We use reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational measures appropriate to the nature
      of the information we maintain to help protect it from unauthorized access, loss, misuse, or
      alteration.
    </p>

    <p>
      No website or internet transmission can be guaranteed to be completely secure. You use the Site at
      your own risk.
    </p>

    <h2>13. Visitors Outside the United States</h2>
    <p>
      The Site is operated from the United States and is primarily intended for visitors in the United
      States. If you visit the Site from another jurisdiction, please be aware that your information may
      be processed in the United States or other locations where our service providers operate.
    </p>

    <h2>14. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the "Last
      updated" date at the top of this page. Continued use of the Site after an update means you accept
      the revised Policy.
    </p>

    <h2>15. Contact</h2>
    <p>If you have questions or requests related to this Privacy Policy or your information, contact:</p>

    <p>
      <strong>Musifer</strong><br>
      Operated by <strong>Everett Ballance</strong><br>
      Email: contact@musifer.studio<br>
      Location: Idaho, United States
    </p>

